e details: https://requests.readthedocs.io/en/latest/user/advanced/#proxies\n```\n"]}, {"name": "pypdns.api.PyPDNS.iter_query", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "q", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "filter_rrtype", "type": {"name": "str | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "break_on_errors", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "Generator", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Generator", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "PDNSRecord", "xref": {"fqname": "pypdns.api.PDNSRecord", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "dict[str, str | int] | None", "xref": null, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Iterate over all the recording matching your request, useful if there are a lot.\nNote: the order is non-deterministic.\n\n```\nparam q\n\nThe query\n\nparam filter_rrtype\n\nThe filter, must be a valid RR Type or the response will be empty.\n\nparam break_on_errors\n\nIf there is an error, stop iterating and break immediately\n```\n"]}, {"name": "pypdns.api.PyPDNS._query", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "q", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "sort_by", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "filter_rrtype", "type": {"name": "str | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "